Terminals unused in grammar

   FIXED
   ENSEMBLE
   PLAY
   SCORE
   TYPE_INT
   TYPE_FLOAT
   TYPE_BOOL
   TYPE_STRING


Grammar

    0 $accept: program $end

    1 program: program flow_definition
    2        | /* empty */

    3 flow_definition: FLOW IDENTIFIER parameter_part block

    4 parameter_part: TAKE LPAREN parameter_list_opt RPAREN
    5               | /* empty */

    6 parameter_list_opt: parameter_list
    7                   | /* empty */

    8 parameter_list: parameter_list COMMA IDENTIFIER
    9               | IDENTIFIER

   10 block: LBRACE statement_list RBRACE

   11 statement_list: statement_list statement
   12               | /* empty */

   13 statement: NOTE IDENTIFIER ASSIGN expression SEMICOLON
   14          | STAGE IDENTIFIER ASSIGN expression SEMICOLON
   15          | EMIT expression SEMICOLON
   16          | RETURN expression SEMICOLON
   17          | RETURN SEMICOLON
   18          | IDENTIFIER LPAREN arg_list_opt RPAREN SEMICOLON
   19          | BREAK SEMICOLON
   20          | CONTINUE SEMICOLON
   21          | branch_statement
   22          | repeat_statement

   23 branch_statement: BRANCH LPAREN expression RPAREN block
   24                 | BRANCH LPAREN expression RPAREN block ELSEWISE block

   25 repeat_statement: REPEAT LPAREN expression RPAREN block

   26 expression: logic_or

   27 logic_or: logic_or OR logic_and
   28         | logic_and

   29 logic_and: logic_and AND equality
   30          | equality

   31 equality: equality EQ relational
   32         | equality NE relational
   33         | relational

   34 relational: additive rel_tail

   35 rel_tail: rel_tail relop additive
   36         | /* empty */

   37 relop: LT
   38      | LE
   39      | GT
   40      | GE

   41 additive: additive PLUS term
   42         | additive MINUS term
   43         | term

   44 term: term MUL unary
   45     | term DIV unary
   46     | unary

   47 unary: MINUS unary
   48      | NOT unary
   49      | primary

   50 primary: LPAREN expression RPAREN
   51        | TRUE
   52        | FALSE
   53        | NUMBER
   54        | STRING_LITERAL
   55        | IDENTIFIER LPAREN arg_list_opt RPAREN
   56        | IDENTIFIER

   57 arg_list_opt: arg_list
   58             | /* empty */

   59 arg_list: arg_list COMMA expression
   60         | expression


